data.description: Spectacular home in what is arguably Key West's finest Casa Marina neighborhood.  3,257 square feet (nearly twice the size of a typical Key West home) of high-end finishes around the corner from Dog Beach and Louie's Backyard and a short walk to Duval.  Exotic woods, marble, granites, soaring ceilings, and tropical ambiance are found throughout.  A giant chef's eat-in kitchen (500 sq ft!) with marble floors, Arctic blue ice granite countertops, vaulted pine ceilings, and an outdoor deck is an entertaining dream.  Huge formal living room, a sunny family room that opens to the pool deck and stone waterfall. A large and beautiful full second kitchen and a 2 bedroom renovated guest wing with a full private bath round out the main floor living spaces.  Two separate and massive upstairs Master Suites with vaulted cedar ceilings (masterpieces unto themselves) and large closets provide unparalleled sleeping quarters while the rear Master has a balcony overlooking the pool.  Two spacious attics offer ample storage.  Built like a fortress with hurricane and termite-repellent materials, this gorgeous home was recently rebuilt to last and no hurricane this century has reached it's door.  All five bathrooms feature marble tile from around the world.  The house has two LEGAL units to be used as a duplex (with separate entrances), or a very spacious single-family home (with up to 6 bedrooms).  Mother-in-Law suite, or nursery wing on main floor.  The backyard oasis provides a peaceful, tropical setting to relax and unwind--off-street parking for three cars. A must-see villa that will not last long; catch it while you can.  One of the owners is a Florida Licensed Realtor and the Listing Agent.
